My Meme

The Meme that I have made is a take on the classic Hotline Bling Drake meme template only that I used a bad computer science joke instead. 

library(magick)

# first image
drake_yes <- image_read("https://i.cbc.ca/1.3279853.1532811524!/fileImage/httpImage/image.jpg_gen/derivatives/16x9_780/drake.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(1000)

# second image
drake_no <- image_read("https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wAbnNZDhYrA/maxresdefault.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(1000)

#create the text boxes
front_end <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                         height = 500, 
                         color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "FRONT-END",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

back_end <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                        height = 500, 
                        color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "BACK-END",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

week_end <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                        height = 500, 
                        color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "WEEK-END",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# put the text next to equivalent image
first_row <- c(drake_no, front_end) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(drake_no, back_end) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(drake_yes, week_end) %>%
  image_append()

# stack rows 
meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# save the meme as a PNG file
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

This animated GIF is of a stick figure athlete who competes in a long jump event and wins a trophy it was made with 6 frames. 

library(magick)

counts <- 1:4 %>% as.character()

# adding images
walking_image <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2014/03/25/16/31/stick-man-297255_1280.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)

running_image <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1226131725/vector/a-running-stick-figure.jpg?s=170667a&w=0&k=20&c=qac-Aizufupnz4S1whG5qZnrL2oZOc22rcch9DQgvZE=") %>%
  image_scale(500)

jumping_image <- image_read("https://www.seekpng.com/png/full/66-664200_jumping-dancer-comments-stick-man-jumping.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)

falling_image <- image_read("https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/thumbnails/011/395/748/small/falling-man-icon-free-vector.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

lying_image <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSuhzSWXnJE5fr-6w3bOZrBU93_MgK6E_zv4A&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_scale(500)

trophy_image <- image_read("https://www.shareicon.net/data/128x128/2016/02/19/721489_cup_512x512.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# creating all the frames and adjusting sizes
frame1 <- walking_image %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- running_image %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500") 

frame3 <- jumping_image %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- falling_image %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500") 

frame5 <- lying_image %>%
  image_scale(500)

frame6 <- trophy_image %>%
  image_scale(500)

# ordering the frames
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5, frame6)

# making animation with frames per second
animation = image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

#saving animation as a GIF
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
